1
00:01:17,240 --> 00:01:17,920
Uncle Lin,

2
00:01:18,480 --> 00:01:19,740
please have some food.

3
00:01:43,680 --> 00:01:44,280
Wangshu,

4
00:01:45,160 --> 00:01:46,890
come inside and have some food.

5
00:01:49,160 --> 00:01:50,039
I can't eat.

6
00:01:52,360 --> 00:01:54,080
You are pregnant.

7
00:01:54,479 --> 00:01:55,720
For the sake of the baby,

8
00:01:55,720 --> 00:01:57,200
you must eat something.

9
00:02:21,400 --> 00:02:22,860
Quanzhou has been bombed.

10
00:02:24,079 --> 00:02:25,680
Malaya is also not peaceful.

11
00:02:26,040 --> 00:02:26,720
Jiadong,

12
00:02:27,200 --> 00:02:28,800
will he be in danger?

13
00:02:37,960 --> 00:02:39,220
I really didn't expect

14
00:02:39,720 --> 00:02:41,280
that the control of penicillin

15
00:02:41,280 --> 00:02:42,540
would be so strict now.

16
00:02:42,640 --> 00:02:44,170
The Chinese clinics we know

17
00:02:44,360 --> 00:02:45,480
are all sold out.

18
00:02:45,680 --> 00:02:47,140
We can't buy a single dose.

19
00:02:47,400 --> 00:02:49,200
What about the Malayan clinics?

20
00:02:49,400 --> 00:02:50,530
Not working either.

21
00:02:50,760 --> 00:02:51,800
You need a special permit

22
00:02:51,800 --> 00:02:53,530
from the Malayan authorities.

23
00:02:53,760 --> 00:02:55,600
Even if you get the permit,

24
00:02:55,800 --> 00:02:56,400
one clinic

25
00:02:56,640 --> 00:02:58,480
can only sell you two doses at most.

26
00:02:58,480 --> 00:03:00,000
That's far from enough.

27
00:03:01,200 --> 00:03:02,200
It's wartime now.

28
00:03:02,840 --> 00:03:03,500
Penicillin

29
00:03:03,560 --> 00:03:05,290
is a strictly controlled drug.

30
00:03:06,200 --> 00:03:07,930
We have to think of another way.

31
00:03:08,120 --> 00:03:09,360
What else can we do?

32
00:03:10,720 --> 00:03:11,880
The Chinese clinics don't have it,

33
00:03:11,880 --> 00:03:13,640
and we can't buy it from Malayan clinics.

34
00:03:13,640 --> 00:03:15,040
What do you suggest we do?

35
00:03:17,240 --> 00:03:18,000
Britain.

36
00:03:18,880 --> 00:03:20,410
We can buy from the British.

37
00:03:21,040 --> 00:03:21,840
Malaya

38
00:03:21,920 --> 00:03:23,320
is a British colony.

39
00:03:24,880 --> 00:03:26,640
It's a very tense period now.

40
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:28,200
Look at the Japanese,

41
00:03:28,200 --> 00:03:29,240
running amok.

42
00:03:29,680 --> 00:03:30,640
The British are somewhat

43
00:03:30,640 --> 00:03:32,079
wary of the Japanese.

44
00:03:32,160 --> 00:03:33,440
I'm afraid even if they have the medicine,

45
00:03:33,440 --> 00:03:34,920
they won't sell it to us.

46
00:03:35,240 --> 00:03:37,200
But Britain is a neutral country now.

47
00:03:37,200 --> 00:03:38,320
No matter how domineering the Japanese are,

48
00:03:38,320 --> 00:03:38,840
they can't control

49
00:03:38,840 --> 00:03:40,079
the British pharmacies.

50
00:03:40,079 --> 00:03:41,720
Besides, as long as there's money to be made,

51
00:03:41,720 --> 00:03:42,560
the British aren't controlled

52
00:03:42,560 --> 00:03:43,720
by the Malayan authorities.

53
00:03:43,720 --> 00:03:44,360
Jiadong.

54
00:03:46,440 --> 00:03:47,840
Jiadong's idea is great.

55
00:03:48,280 --> 00:03:48,810
Lao Zhao,

56
00:03:48,840 --> 00:03:49,480
go right now

57
00:03:49,480 --> 00:03:50,920
to the British man George's pharmacy.

58
00:03:50,920 --> 00:03:51,880
Make an appointment for me to meet his manager,

59
00:03:51,880 --> 00:03:52,480
Mr. Peter,

60
00:03:52,680 --> 00:03:53,810
as soon as possible.

61
00:03:53,840 --> 00:03:54,440
Okay.

62
00:04:02,400 --> 00:04:03,560
Mr. Peter, please.

63
00:04:08,800 --> 00:04:09,440
Mr. Peter.

64
00:04:10,560 --> 00:04:11,490
Long time no see.

65
00:04:11,720 --> 00:04:13,050
How is business lately?

66
00:04:13,480 --> 00:04:14,800
As you Chinese say,

67
00:04:14,880 --> 00:04:15,680
so-so.

68
00:04:16,360 --> 00:04:17,019
Have a seat.

69
00:04:18,200 --> 00:04:19,079
This is a

70
00:04:19,320 --> 00:04:21,250
traditional Chinese restaurant.

71
00:04:21,320 --> 00:04:23,160
They make very authentic

72
00:04:23,400 --> 00:04:24,800
Chinese Minnan cuisine.

73
00:04:25,040 --> 00:04:26,360
I wanted to invite you, Mr. Peter,

74
00:04:26,360 --> 00:04:27,080
to try it.

75
00:04:27,920 --> 00:04:28,720
Chairman Qin,

76
00:04:28,840 --> 00:04:29,880
you wouldn't treat me

77
00:04:29,880 --> 00:04:30,920
to a meal for no reason.

78
00:04:30,920 --> 00:04:31,720
Of course not.

79
00:04:32,120 --> 00:04:33,520
I have a big business deal

80
00:04:33,760 --> 00:04:34,920
for you, Mr. Peter.

81
00:04:35,880 --> 00:04:36,600
A big deal?

82
00:04:37,240 --> 00:04:38,120
What kind of business?

83
00:04:38,120 --> 00:04:39,120
Have some tea first.

84
00:04:39,120 --> 00:04:40,040
This is from Fujian, China,

85
00:04:40,040 --> 00:04:41,520
premium Fuding white tea.

86
00:04:41,680 --> 00:04:42,240
Try it.

87
00:04:42,840 --> 00:04:44,640
We British also love tea,

88
00:04:44,880 --> 00:04:46,120
but we only drink

89
00:04:46,200 --> 00:04:47,400
British black tea.

90
00:04:48,120 --> 00:04:49,840
When the Chinese were drinking white tea,

91
00:04:49,840 --> 00:04:51,640
Mr. Lipton wasn't even born yet.

92
00:05:02,720 --> 00:05:04,250
These are Japanese planes.

93
00:05:04,760 --> 00:05:06,360
Quanzhou is going to suffer.

94
00:05:10,720 --> 00:05:11,920
Ancestors, bless us.

95
00:05:12,200 --> 00:05:13,260
Bless my hometown.

96
00:05:13,480 --> 00:05:14,640
Bless my Jiadong.

97
00:05:17,320 --> 00:05:18,800
I want to buy

98
00:05:18,920 --> 00:05:20,600
a batch of medicine from Mr. Peter.

99
00:05:20,600 --> 00:05:22,060
Medicine? What medicine?

100
00:05:22,240 --> 00:05:23,000
Penicillin.

101
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:24,730
Penicillin?

102
00:05:25,480 --> 00:05:26,120
Yes.

103
00:05:27,080 --> 00:05:28,320
President Qin, you should know

104
00:05:28,320 --> 00:05:29,380
that it's wartime.

105
00:05:29,520 --> 00:05:30,380
Penicillin is a

106
00:05:30,400 --> 00:05:31,660
controlled medicine.

107
00:05:32,040 --> 00:05:33,680
It can't be bought elsewhere.

108
00:05:33,680 --> 00:05:34,320
That's why

109
00:05:35,360 --> 00:05:36,640
I came to Mr. Peter

110
00:05:37,200 --> 00:05:38,280
for this business.

111
00:05:39,120 --> 00:05:40,580
How much do you want to buy?

112
00:05:41,000 --> 00:05:42,200
The more, the better.

113
00:05:43,159 --> 00:05:44,880
But I only have two boxes now.

114
00:05:45,040 --> 00:05:45,720
400 doses.

115
00:05:46,280 --> 00:05:46,760
Okay.

116
00:05:46,960 --> 00:05:48,820
Then leave these two boxes for me.

117
00:05:49,159 --> 00:05:51,490
I'll take as much as you have in the future.

118
00:05:52,960 --> 00:05:54,320
Are you buying for your

119
00:05:54,320 --> 00:05:56,760
Chinese resistance army by any chance?

120
00:05:57,520 --> 00:05:58,120
Mr. Peter.

121
00:05:58,280 --> 00:05:59,760
You and I are both businessmen.

122
00:05:59,760 --> 00:06:01,960
We just make money and ask no questions.

123
00:06:04,160 --> 00:06:06,020
Make money? How much can you make?

124
00:06:08,280 --> 00:06:08,960
Jiadong.

125
00:06:14,680 --> 00:06:15,640
Thank you.

126
00:06:22,080 --> 00:06:22,810
This is my...

127
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:23,800
For Mr. Peter,

128
00:06:23,840 --> 00:06:24,900
as a personal gift.

129
00:06:25,080 --> 00:06:26,080
I will pay for

130
00:06:26,440 --> 00:06:27,900
the medicine separately.

131
00:06:28,040 --> 00:06:28,640
No.

132
00:06:29,520 --> 00:06:30,650
I can't accept this.

133
00:06:31,400 --> 00:06:32,320
I will pay you

134
00:06:32,760 --> 00:06:34,440
double the current market price

135
00:06:34,440 --> 00:06:35,440
for the medicine.

136
00:06:35,640 --> 00:06:36,159
Double?

137
00:06:36,320 --> 00:06:36,880
Yes,

138
00:06:37,480 --> 00:06:38,480
and in cash.

139
00:06:39,840 --> 00:06:40,320
Okay,

140
00:06:40,600 --> 00:06:42,800
but I can't deliver everything at once.

141
00:06:42,840 --> 00:06:43,400
Deal.

142
00:06:46,560 --> 00:06:47,760
Cheers.

143
00:06:51,480 --> 00:06:52,440
Jiadong should have

144
00:06:52,440 --> 00:06:53,840
arrived in Malaya by now.

145
00:06:55,880 --> 00:06:57,680
He should have arrived long ago.

146
00:06:58,600 --> 00:07:00,260
Under normal circumstances,

147
00:07:00,520 --> 00:07:02,580
he should be taking a ship back by now.

148
00:07:03,200 --> 00:07:05,200
I really hope nothing happens to him

149
00:07:05,480 --> 00:07:06,880
and he can come back soon.

150
00:07:07,560 --> 00:07:08,280
He will.

151
00:07:09,200 --> 00:07:09,730
Jiadong,

152
00:07:10,120 --> 00:07:12,180
he will definitely come back safely.

153
00:07:19,640 --> 00:07:20,320
Wangshu,

154
00:07:21,640 --> 00:07:22,240
Wangshu!

155
00:07:22,840 --> 00:07:24,170
Wangshu, what's wrong?

156
00:07:24,800 --> 00:07:25,600
What's wrong?

157
00:07:26,640 --> 00:07:27,640
My stomach hurts.

158
00:07:28,280 --> 00:07:29,340
Thank you, Mr. Qin.

159
00:07:29,520 --> 00:07:31,280
On behalf of the soldiers fighting on the front line,

160
00:07:31,280 --> 00:07:31,940
I thank you.

161
00:07:32,120 --> 00:07:34,240
In times of national crisis, everyone is responsible.

162
00:07:34,240 --> 00:07:35,200
Mr. Li, please sit down.

163
00:07:35,200 --> 00:07:35,760
Okay.

164
00:07:39,560 --> 00:07:40,960
With this batch of medicine,

165
00:07:40,960 --> 00:07:42,120
we can save the lives of more

166
00:07:42,120 --> 00:07:44,180
soldiers fighting on the front line.

167
00:07:44,440 --> 00:07:45,280
So Mr. Qin,

168
00:07:46,280 --> 00:07:48,320
you are also a hero of the resistance.

169
00:07:48,320 --> 00:07:49,520
I wouldn't dare claim that.

170
00:07:49,520 --> 00:07:50,520
I am also Chinese.

171
00:07:50,680 --> 00:07:51,880
Resisting the enemy and saving the country

172
00:07:51,880 --> 00:07:54,140
is the responsibility of every Chinese.

173
00:07:55,120 --> 00:07:56,000
Jiadong told me

174
00:07:56,240 --> 00:07:58,080
you paid a high price for this medicine.

175
00:07:58,080 --> 00:07:59,080
As for the cost...

176
00:08:00,240 --> 00:08:01,570
Jiadong talks too much.

177
00:08:01,600 --> 00:08:03,760
It's a small matter, not worth mentioning.

178
00:08:03,760 --> 00:08:04,760
As for this batch of medicine,

179
00:08:04,760 --> 00:08:07,760
let's quickly find a way to send it back to our country.

180
00:08:07,960 --> 00:08:08,640
Mr. Qin,

181
00:08:09,520 --> 00:08:11,000
I have important news to tell you.

182
00:08:11,000 --> 00:08:11,930
Please go ahead.

183
00:08:12,960 --> 00:08:14,720
The current situation is very critical.

184
00:08:14,720 --> 00:08:15,880
According to intelligence,

185
00:08:15,880 --> 00:08:17,320
the Japanese have decided to attack Malaya

186
00:08:17,320 --> 00:08:18,240
in December.

187
00:08:20,080 --> 00:08:21,080
The plan to invade Southeast Asia

188
00:08:21,080 --> 00:08:22,360
has been brought forward.

189
00:08:22,360 --> 00:08:23,290
We are also ready

190
00:08:23,560 --> 00:08:25,220
for underground resistance.

191
00:08:25,400 --> 00:08:27,130
You must also make plans early.

192
00:08:27,600 --> 00:08:28,320
I see.

193
00:08:29,200 --> 00:08:29,800
Mr. Qin,

194
00:08:30,280 --> 00:08:31,610
I have another request.

195
00:08:32,480 --> 00:08:33,039
Tell me.

196
00:08:33,480 --> 00:08:34,600
As long as our Overseas Chinese Chamber of Commerce

197
00:08:34,600 --> 00:08:35,130
can do it,

198
00:08:35,240 --> 00:08:36,299
we are duty-bound.

199
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:39,600
The current maritime traffic routes

200
00:08:39,760 --> 00:08:40,720
have been blockaded and controlled

201
00:08:40,720 --> 00:08:41,679
by the Japanese.

202
00:08:42,840 --> 00:08:44,560
The traffic routes of our resistance organization

203
00:08:44,560 --> 00:08:45,800
have also been destroyed by the Japanese.

204
00:08:45,800 --> 00:08:46,480
Therefore,

205
00:08:47,240 --> 00:08:48,160
we have no way now

206
00:08:48,160 --> 00:08:50,360
to send the medicine back to our country.

207
00:08:50,360 --> 00:08:51,080
But

208
00:08:51,680 --> 00:08:54,720
the domestic resistance is in urgent need of medicine.

209
00:08:54,720 --> 00:08:55,320
Yes.

210
00:08:56,200 --> 00:08:57,600
The only way now

211
00:08:58,640 --> 00:09:00,570
is to go through the Qiaopi Bureau.

212
00:09:00,800 --> 00:09:01,860
The Qiaopi Bureau?

213
00:09:02,840 --> 00:09:03,440
Yes.

214
00:09:03,840 --> 00:09:05,370
We can use the Qiaopi Bureau

215
00:09:05,480 --> 00:09:07,400
to secretly transport this medicine

216
00:09:07,400 --> 00:09:08,530
back to the country.

217
00:09:15,560 --> 00:09:16,560
I will deliver it.

218
00:09:17,720 --> 00:09:19,560
All passenger ships are suspended.

219
00:09:19,560 --> 00:09:21,020
There is only one ship left

220
00:09:21,040 --> 00:09:22,240
returning to Xiamen.

221
00:09:22,280 --> 00:09:24,320
It's docked at the freight terminal.

222
00:09:24,320 --> 00:09:25,520
The sea is not safe either.

223
00:09:25,520 --> 00:09:26,880
There could be Japanese planes at any time.

224
00:09:26,880 --> 00:09:28,480
You need to be extra careful.

225
00:09:28,520 --> 00:09:29,200
I will.

226
00:09:29,720 --> 00:09:30,850
Besides medicines,

227
00:09:31,160 --> 00:09:32,320
there is also some money in here.

228
00:09:32,320 --> 00:09:34,520
It was all donated by overseas Chinese.

229
00:09:34,840 --> 00:09:36,320
You need to hand it all over to

230
00:09:36,320 --> 00:09:38,160
the anti-Japanese soldiers in the country.

231
00:09:38,160 --> 00:09:38,840
Tell them

232
00:09:39,120 --> 00:09:40,560
as long as the sea route is still open,

233
00:09:40,560 --> 00:09:42,480
Chinese businessmen will definitely do their best

234
00:09:42,480 --> 00:09:44,040
to raise the supplies they need.

235
00:09:44,040 --> 00:09:44,770
Don't worry.

236
00:09:44,880 --> 00:09:45,600
As long as I am here,

237
00:09:45,600 --> 00:09:46,440
the medicines and money

238
00:09:46,440 --> 00:09:47,640
will not be missing at all.

239
00:09:47,640 --> 00:09:49,200
After arriving at the Xiamen freight terminal,

240
00:09:49,200 --> 00:09:50,520
it will be a bit hard for you.

241
00:09:50,520 --> 00:09:52,360
You have to travel a mountain road to enter the city.

242
00:09:52,360 --> 00:09:54,360
Do you remember the delivery address?

243
00:09:54,360 --> 00:09:56,120
I remember. Xiamen Puji Clinic.

244
00:09:56,120 --> 00:09:57,040
I know the address.

245
00:09:57,040 --> 00:09:58,000
Mr. Li instructed

246
00:09:58,000 --> 00:09:58,720
that it must be given to

247
00:09:58,720 --> 00:10:00,040
Dr. Fu at the clinic.

248
00:10:00,640 --> 00:10:01,320
I know.

249
00:10:05,000 --> 00:10:05,600
Mr. Qin,

250
00:10:05,800 --> 00:10:06,600
Manager Zhao,

251
00:10:06,880 --> 00:10:07,840
you two have always been

252
00:10:07,840 --> 00:10:09,300
my most respected elders.

253
00:10:09,480 --> 00:10:11,610
You must take good care of yourselves.

254
00:10:33,120 --> 00:10:33,840
Jiadong.

255
00:10:35,200 --> 00:10:36,640
When will you come back?

256
00:10:38,480 --> 00:10:39,880
Where on earth are you?
